erging political and social institutions that culminated in the creation of a unitary empire.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aFloodsxFolklorexChina. 0aFloodsxReligious aspectsxChinaxChina. 0aFloodszChinavFolklore. 0aFloodszChinaxReligious aspects. 4aAsian Studies : Asian Religion and Philosophy. 7aRELIGION / Eastern.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780791482223?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780791482223423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780791482223/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles